<TITLE> Oil spill in Texas port after crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TEXAS, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)--Hazardous materials crews work to clean up a large oil spill in Texas waters following the collision between a barge and a tanker. A clean up operation is underway in Texas after a major oil spill. Tonnes of crude oil leaked into the water when a tanker collided with a towing vessel pushing two barges near Port Arthur at the weekend. A large hole was torn in the side of the tanker. No one was injured in the collision. The vessel was carrying 80,000 barrels of crude oil to Exxon Mobil's refinery in nearby Beaumont. But it's not clear exactly how much oil was disgorged into the water. Vapours from the spill triggered warnings of a hydrogen sulphide release near the port, prompting authorities to evacuate some residents for several hours. The busy waterway, which serves four refineries in Port Arthur and nearby Beaumont, remains shut. Around 150 barges and 15 tankers pass through the narrow stretch everyday. The oil hub, which lies 90 miles east of Houston, has a combined refining capacity equal to about 6.5 cent of the total US capacity. The cause of the collision is under investigat
